escribes her burial in her garden, which took place without religious or revolutionary ceremony in the presence of all her favourite pets.Most of the newly discovered letters are addressed to HelvTtius by figures as important as d'Alembert, Boulanger, Chastellux, Saint-Lambert, Servan, Thieriot, and Trublet. Some of these complete an existing exchange, others provide dates for letters already published.The fifth and final volume will be devoted primarily to a comprehensive index. It will also include a chronological list of all the letters, corrections and modifications, and other useful material.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aPhilosopherszFrancevCorrespondence. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Letters.2bisacsh1 aAllan, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDainard, Alan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aInguenaud, Marie-Thérèse, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOrsoni, Jean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSmith, David , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144267351940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442673519423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442673519.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK